    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Antibody-deficient patients respond poorly to COVID-19 vaccination and are at risk of severe or prolonged infection. Prophylaxis with anti-SARS-CoV-2 monoclonal antibodies has been considered. We here demonstrate that many immunoglobulin preparations now contain neutralising anti-SARS-CoV-2 antibodies which are transmitted to patients in good concentrations, albeit with significant differences between products.</jats:p>",
